The paper proposes a solution that combines AI and IoT technologies for traffic light control, which is an essential component of intelligent transportation systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed solution uses distributed multi-agent Q learning, which falls under the category of reinforcement learning, and can be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The solution also involves optimizing the performance of the entire control system, which can be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper mentions the use of surveillance cameras, which can be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the solution involves considering many constraints/rules for traffic light control in the real world, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
